IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: PROVIDE HEALTH SERVICES TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH OF ASIAN PACIFIC ISLANDER AND OTHER COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: DEEPLY ROOTED IN THE ASIAN PACIFIC ISLANDER COMMUNITY, ICHS PROVIDES CULTURALLY AND LINGUISTICALLY APPROPRIATE HEALTH AND WELLNESS SERVICES AND PROMOTES HEALTH EQUITY FOR ALL.
IRS990.Desc: ICHS PROVIDES MEDICAL SERVICES TO PEOPLE, REGARDLESS OF ABILITY TO PAY. THESE SERVICES INCLUDE PHYSICAL EXAMS, IMMUNIZATIONS, MINOR SURGERY, HOME VISITS, INFANT AND WELL-CHILD CHECK-UPS, OBSTETRIC AND GERIATRIC CARE. DURING 2022, ICHS PROVIDED 70,397 PRIMARY HEALTH CARE VISITS TO PATIENTS AND $246,339 OF CHARITY CARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: ICHS PROVIDES FULL DENTAL CARE FOR THE ENTIRE FAMILY, INCLUDING EXTENSIVE DENTURE WORK, FULL CLEANING FOR ADULTS AND CHILDREN, PREVENTATIVE DENTISTRY, MINOR ORAL SURGERY, RESTORATIVE SERVICES, ORTHODONTIA, AND EMERGENCY CARE. ICHS ALSO BRINGS DENTAL SERVICES INTO KING COUNTY COMMUNITIES AND SCHOOLS WITH ITS MOBILE DENTAL CLINIC, AS WELL AS ORAL HEALTH EDUCATION IN THE COMMUNITY. DURING 2022, ICHS PROVIDED 41,073 DENTAL CARE VISITS TO PATIENTS AND $436,617 OF CHARITY CARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: ICHS PROVIDES A VARIETY OF OTHER HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO THE COMMUNITY INCLUDING ACUPUNCTURE, VISION, DISEASE PREVENTION, HEALTH EDUCATION, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH, NUTRITION SERVICES, AND FAMILY PLANNING FOR TEENS AND ADULTS. DURING 2022, ICHS PROVIDED 9,090 HEALTH CARE VISITS TO PATIENTS AND $42,565 OF CHARITY CARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: ICHS' HEALTHY AGING & WELLNESS PROGRAM (HAWP) MEETS THE UNIQUE NEEDS OF ADULTS AGE 55 AND OLDER. SERVICES INCLUDE:- PACE (PROGRAM OF ALL-INCLUSIVE CARE FOR THE ELDERLY) - INDIVIDUALIZED SERVICES TO KEEP NURSING-HOME ELIGIBLE ELDERS LIVING INDEPENDENTLY AT HOME OR IN THE COMMUNITY. PACE HAD 1,143 MEMBER MONTHS IN 2022.- ASSISTED LIVING AT LEGACY HOUSE - SENIOR-FRIENDLY LIVING SPACE WITH 24/7 SERVICES TO SUPPORT RESIDENTS TO LIVE INDEPENDENTLY AND SAFELY IN CULTURALLY-FAMILIAR SURROUNDINGS. - ADULT DAY SERVICES FOR SENIORS WITH CHANGING PHYSICAL OR COGNITIVE ABILITIES THRIVE AND CAREGIVERS WITH RESPITE. SERVICES INCLUDE FITNESS, SOCIAL AND RECREATIONAL GROUP ACTIVITIES, NUTRITIOUS, ASIAN-STYLE LUNCHES, TRANSPORTATION COORDINATION, RN OVERSIGHT, REHABILITATIVE OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY, PERSONAL CARE SERVICES, RESPITE FOR CAREGIVERS, ADULT NUTRITION.- EBSHP (EVIDENCE-BASED SENIOR HEALTH PROMOTION) SUCH AS TAI JI QUAN: MOVING FOR BETTER BALANCE (WEEKLY CLASSES TO HELP SENIORS IMPROVE MUSCLE STRENGTH, BALANCE, FLEXIBILITY, MOBILITY, AND REDUCE RISK OF FALLS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DURING THE FISCAL YEAR, INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY HEALTH SERVICES ("ICHS") STAFF ATTENDED THE APA LEGISLATIVE DAY; SUPPORTED ADVOCACY ORGANIZATIONS, COORDINATED MEETINGS BETWEEN MEMBERS OF CONGRESS AND SENIOR ICHS STAFF AND BOARD MEMBERS; DEVELOPED REQUESTS FOR INFORMATION ON SPECIFIC LEGISLATION AND ISSUES FROM MEMBERS OF CONGRESS OR THEIR STAFF; PARTCIPATED IN MEETINGS; COMMUNICATED CALLS TO ACTION TO ICHS STAFF ON ADVOCACY ISSUES ESSENTIAL TO ICHS BUSINESS ACTIVITIES (CHC FUNDING REAUTHORIZATION; AND COORDINATED ICHS'S SUPPORT FOR CALLS TO ACTION ON APPROXIMATELY A DOZEN ADVOCACY ISSUES AS LED BY OTHER ORGANIZATIONS.

THE ORGANIZATION HAS RECEIVED A DETERMINATION LETTER FROM THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS) THAT STATES IT IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC). ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES IS SHOWN IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT EVALUATED THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX POSITIONS AND CONCLUDED THAT THE ORGANIZATION HAD TAKEN NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT REQUIRE ADJUSTMENTS TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS TO COMPLY WITH THE PROVISIONS OF TOPIC 740 OF THE ACCOUNTING STANDARDS CODIFICATION (ASC).

AT THE DISCRETION OF THE ICHS BOARD, THE CEO RECEIVES PERFORMANCE BONUSES NOT TO EXCEED 20% OF THE CEO ANNUAL SALARY FOR THE CALENDAR YEAR. THE PERFORMANCE BONUS CRITERIA ARE AS FOLLOWS: - FINANCIAL: REMAIN WITHIN 5% OF THE APPROVED ICHS ANNUAL BUDGET OR EXPECTED MARGIN - STRATEGY: PRESENTATION OF YEARLY IMPLEMENTATION PLAN AND PROGRESS ON AT LEAST 3 INITIATIVES - COMMUNITY: MEET WITH MINIMUM OF 12 EXISTING OR POTENTIAL PARTNERS TO UNDERSTAND COMMUNITY NEEDS AND REPORT BACK TO THE BOARD - PEOPLE: CONDUCT AND REPORT STAFF SATISFACTION SURVEY (2X A YEAR) AND STAFF TURNOVER OF <25% - QUALITY: MEET OR EXCEED 3 OF 7 QUALITY MEASURES FROM ICHS SCORECARD

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS CHAIRED BY THE CHAIR OF THE BOARD AND ONLY CONSISTS OF THE ELECTED OFFICERS OF THE BOARD AND THE PRESIDENT/CEO OF ICHS AS AN EX OFFICIO MEMBER. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS EXCLUSIVELY AUTHORIZED TO ACT FOR THE BOARD IN URGENT SITUATIONS DURING THE INTERIM PERIOD BETWEEN MEETINGS OF THE BOARD IN A MANNER CONSISTENT WITH ESTABISHED BOARD POLICIES AND/OR DIRECTION, AND SHALL REPORT ALL ACTIVITIES AND ACTIONS AT THE NEXT MEETING OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A DRAFT COPY OF THE FORM 990 WAS REVIEWED BY THE CFO AND DESIGNATED STAFF, INCLUDING THE CONTROLLER. THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCE DEPARTMENT THEN REVIEWED AND SUBMITTED A DRAFT COPY OF THE FORM 990 TO THE FINANCE, AUDIT AND EXECUTIVE COMMITTEES OF THE THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, WHO RECOMMENDED APPROVAL OF THE FORM TO THE FULL BOARD. THE FORM 990 WAS SUBSEQUENTLY PRESENTED TO THE FULL BOARD AT THE FOLLOWING BOARD MEETING FOR REVIEW AND APPROVAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ICHS REGULARLY AND CONSISTENTLY MONITORS AND ENFORCES COMPLIANCE WITH THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES. ICHS HAS TWO CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES. THE FIRST POLICY IS AN OVERARCHING POLICY FOR THE ENTIRE AGENCY, WHICH WORKS TO ENSURE EFFECTIVE MANAGEMENT OF CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AT ICHS. THE SECOND POLICY IS SET TO ENSURE ALL BOARD-RELATED ACTIVITIES ARE CONDUCTED IN A WAY THAT ENSURES COMPLIANCE WITH APPLICABLE LAWS, PRESERVES THE PUBLIC'S TRUST, ENSURES GOOD STEWARDSHIP OF ICHS RESOURCES, AND UPHOLDS HIGH STANDARDS OF CONDUCT AND PERSONAL INTEGRITY AMONG ALL BOARD DIRECTORS AND BOARD ASSOCIATES. THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY REQUIRES ALL EMPLOYEES AND NON-EMPLOYEE REPRESENTATIVES TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST THAT MAY COMPROMISE THEIR JUDGMENT OR IF PERSONAL INTERESTS ARE IN SUBSTANTIAL CONFLICT WITH THE BEST INTERESTS OF ICHS. SIMILARLY, INDIVIDUALS ARE EXPECTED TO REMOVE THEMSELVES FROM A POSITION OF DECISION-MAKING AUTHORITY OR SIGNIFICANT INFLUENCE WITH RESPECT TO ANY CONFLICT SITUATION THAT ARISES. A SITUATION IS CONSIDERED A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IF AN INTEREST OR ACTIVITY INFLUENCES OR APPEARS TO INFLUENCE THE ABILITY OF AN INDIVIDUAL TO EXERCISE OBJECTIVITY OR IMPAIRS THE INDIVIDUAL'S ABILITY TO PERFORM HIS OR HER EMPLOYMENT OR REPRESENTATIVE WORK RESPONSIBILITIES IN THE BEST INTEREST OF ICHS. ANY UNETHICAL ABUSE OF EMPLOYEES OR NON-EMPLOYEE REPRESENTATIVES CAN RESULT IN DISCIPLINARY ACTION (INCLUDING TERMINATION OF EMPLOYMENT). THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY FOR BOARD DIRECTORS AND BOARD ASSOCIATES REQUIRES BOARD DIRECTORS AND ASSOCIATES TO DISCLOSE ANY REAL OR APPARENT CONFLICT OF INTEREST TO THE BOARD AND EXCUSE HIMSELF OR HERSELF FROM VOTING, AS APPROPRIATE. ADDITIONALLY, NO BOARD MEMBER CAN ALSO BE AN EMPLOYEE OR RELATED TO AN EMPLOYEE OF ICHS. IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS PERCEIVED TO EXIST BUT IS NOT DISCLOSED, THE BOARD MAY VOTE WHETHER THERE IS A REAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST. IF THE VOTE IS AFFIRMATIVE, THE BOARD MEMBER IN QUESTION IS NOT ENTITLED TO VOTE ON THAT ISSUE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD REVIEWS AND DETERMINES THE COMPENSATION OF THE CEO BY USING EXTERNAL MARKET DATA. 1) NWRPCA BIENNIAL REGION X HEALTH CENTER SALARY AND BENEFITS SURVEY 2) NACHC HEALTH CENTER SALARY AND BENEFITS REPORT 3) MILLIMAN'S NW HEALTHCARE EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION SURVEY 4) MERCES CONSULTING CEO COMPENSATION FOR FQHCS ICHS HR SETS PAY LEVELS TO THOSE IN THE EXISTING MARKETPLACE BY USING THE FOLLOWING: 1) NWRPCA BIENNIAL REGION X HEALTH CENTER SALARY AND BENEFITS SURVEY 2) NACHC HEALTH CENTER SALARY AND BENEFITS REPORT 3) MILLIMAN'S NW HEALTHCARE EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION SURVEY 4) MILLIMAN'S NW HEALTHCARE COMPENSATION SURVEY ICHS USES AN INDEPENDENT CONSULTANT TO REVIEW ITS COMPENSATION PHILOSOPHY/STRUCTURE EVERY 5 YEARS TO MAINTAIN A COMPENSATION/BENEFITS PROGRAM THAT REMAINS COMPETITIVE TO ATTRACT AND RETAIN TOP TALENT. THE EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION REVIEW PROCESS MOST RECENTLY INCLUDED REVIEW AND APPROVAL BY INDEPENDENT PERSONS, COMPARABILITY DATA AND CONTEMPORANEOUS SUBSTANTIATION IN 2021.
